# Auto commit and push

After completing code changes in this repo, always commit and push to `origin` unless the user explicitly says not to.

- Run `git status` and `git diff` before committing
- Write a concise commit message focused on why
- Push to `origin/main` (or the current branch) after a successful commit
- Skip commit/push if there are no changes, or if the user asked for review-only / question-only work with no edits

Follow the git safety protocol in user rules (no force push, no amend unless allowed, no committing secrets).
